Description: Extends 'SelvarMix' to regularized variable selection in Gaussian
    model-based clustering with complete or incomplete data. Variables are
    ranked using penalized Gaussian mixture models and assigned to the SRUW
    roles: clustering-relevant variables, redundant variables explained by a
    subset of the relevant variables, and independent noise variables.
    Missing values may be missing not at random (MNAR) and modeled through a
    parsimonious class-only MNARz mechanism, under which each mixture component
    has one missingness probability shared across variables. The missingness
    model may be fitted after SRUW role selection or jointly with the SRUW model.
